In this update:
[1] Turkey: (Zonguldak)
[2] Ukraine: (Crimea)
******
[1] Turkey: (Zonguldak)
Date: Tue 22 Jan 2008
Source: OIE, WAHID (World Animal Health Information Database), Disease
Information 2008; 21(4) [edited]
<http://www.oie.int/wahid-prod/public.php?page=weekly_report_index&admin=0>
Highly pathogenic avian influenza, Turkey
-----------------------------------------
Information received on (and dated) 22 Jan 2008 from Assoc Prof Dr Muzaffer
Aydemir, director general, General Directorate of Protection and Control,
Ministry of Agriculture and Rural Affairs, Ankara, Turkey.
Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Start date: 12 Jan 2008
Date of 1st confirmation of the event: 21 Jan 2008
Date submitted to OIE: 22 Jan 2008
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 2 Apr 2007
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: highly pathogenic avian influenza virus, serotype H5N1
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country
New outbreaks
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1: Village, Sazkoy, Caycuma, Zonguldak
Date of start of the outbreak: 12 Jan 2008
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: village
Species: birds
Susceptible: 300
Cases: 13
Deaths: 13
Destroyed: 0
Slaughtered: 0
Affected population: backyard poultry
Outbreak statistics
Species: birds
Apparent morbidity rate: 4.33 per cent
Apparent mortality rate: 4.33 per cent
Apparent case fatality rate: 100 per cent
Proportion susceptible animals lost*: 4.33 per cent
* Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction,
and/or slaughter
Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: contact with wild species
Epidemiological comments: the disease was notified to the Veterinary
Services on 19 Jan 2008. The stamping out started on 22 Jan 2008.
Diagnostic test results:
Laboratory name and type: Etlik Veterinary Control and Research Institute
(national laboratory)
Species: wild species
Test: polymerase chain reaction (PCR)
Test date: 21 Jan 2008
Result: positive
--
communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
